cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision challenges and proposes a new framework for regression in convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for solving these challenges, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for posing continuous output problems, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with closed geometric manifolds, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
